### Test Log Watcher API Endpoints
### Base URL: http://localhost:4000/api

### Check current watcher status
GET http://localhost:4000/api/watcher/status

### Start log watcher
POST http://localhost:4000/api/watcher/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "log_path": "audit.log"
}

### Process single JSON event through pipeline
POST http://localhost:4000/api/events/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "raw_event": "{\"username\":\"testuser\",\"action\":\"write\",\"file\":\"/etc/config\",\"status\":\"denied\"}"
}

### Process multi-line auditd event
POST http://localhost:4000/api/events/process
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "raw_event": "type=SYSCALL msg=audit(1234567890.123:456): arch=c000003e syscall=85 success=no exit=-13\ntype=PATH msg=audit(1234567890.123:456): item=0 name=\"/etc/shadow\""
}

### Fetch recent events
GET http://localhost:4000/api/events/recent?limit=10

### Fetch recent alerts
GET http://localhost:4000/api/alerts/recent?limit=10

### Stop log watcher
POST http://localhost:4000/api/watcher/stop
Content-Type: application/json

{}
